article.description: Florida Gulf Coast beats Jacksonville 81-63 in A-Sun tourney
article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast beats Jacksonville 81-63 in A-Sun tourney
article.linkText: Florida Gulf Coast beats Jacksonville 81-63 in A-Sun tourney
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. -- Marc-Eddy Norelia scored 19 points off the bench, leading four in double-figure scoring as second-seeded Florida Gulf Coast defeated No. 7 seed Jacksonville 81-63 on Tuesday in the quarterfinals of the Atlantic Sun tournament. Florida Gulf Coast (22-9) advances to a Thursday semifinal. The Eagles had lost to Jacksonville in the regular season finale on Saturday, but left little doubt in the playoff. Norelia broke a 22-22 tie with a layup and two free throws as Florida Gulf Coast pulled away to lead 38-34 at halftime. They led by as many as 12 in the second half before Jacksonville fought back to 59-54. But Norelia added a dunk and a layup to cap a 7-2 run and Florida Gulf Coast was in the clear. Julian DeBose and Brett Comer added 14 each for the Eagles. Kori Babineaux led Jacksonville with 20. Jacksonville finished 10-22.
